      • handleTokenRequest

        OAuth2AccessToken handleTokenRequest(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.List<java.lang.String>> parameters,
                                     PublicAPI tools)
        Authenticates the client (if required) and generates an access token. The input parameters should contain a Map of (HTTP) parameters and their values. For client credentials : CLIENT-ID - ID of the client requesting the token CLIENT_SECRET - Secret of the Client requesting the token On successful authentication, an access token is generated and returned. If the authentication fails, an appropriate error code is returned.
        Parameters:
        parameters - a Map of (HTTP) parameters and their values
        tools - provide requestor context
        Returns:
        An OAuth2AccessToken object containing the token info

      • handleTokenRevocation

        OAuth2RevokeTokenStatus handleTokenRevocation(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.List<java.lang.String>> parameters)
        Authenticates the client (if required) and revoke an access token. The input parameters should contain a Map of (HTTP) parameters and their values. For client credentials : CLIENT-ID - ID of the client for the token CLIENT_SECRET - Secret of the Client for the token On successful authentication, an access token is revoked. If the authentication fails, an appropriate error code is returned.
        Parameters:
        parameters - a Map of (HTTP) parameters and their values
        Returns:
        An OAuth2AccessToken object containing the token info

        Authenticates the client (if required) and introspects an access token. The input parameters should contain a Map of (HTTP) parameters and their values. For client credentials : CLIENT-ID - ID of the client for the token CLIENT_SECRET - Secret of the Client for the token On successful authentication, an access token is revoked. If the authentication fails, an appropriate error code is returned.
